Clumpy-sphere examples for LaRT_v2.00
======================================

Physical setup
--------------
A point source at the centre of a sphere of radius rmax emits Lyman-alpha
photons (or another resonance line) at line centre.  The sphere contains N
non-overlapping spherical clumps of radius clump_radius, placed by
Random Sequential Adsorption (RSA).  Each clump has uniform opacity,
temperature par%temperature, and optionally a bulk velocity set by
clump_sigma_v or velocity_type.  Outside the clumps the medium is vacuum.

The per-clump opacity is set by exactly one of three mutually exclusive
parameters (priority order: first positive value wins):
  clump_tau0  -- line-centre tau from clump centre to surface (dimensionless)
  clump_NHI   -- per-clump HI column density [cm^-2] from centre to surface
                 (do NOT confuse with N_HImax, the system-level column density)
  clump_nH    -- clump hydrogen number density [cm^-3] (requires distance_unit)

The key dimensionless parameters are:
  N_cov  = (3/4) * N_clumps * (clump_radius / rmax)^2  -- line-of-sight
                                                            covering factor
  tau0   = clump_tau0                                   -- per-clump opacity
  sigma_v                                               -- clump velocity dispersion

Activate with par%use_clump_medium = .true.  (LaRT_v2.00 procedure-pointer interface).
The OOP interface par%grid_type = 'clump' is available in LaRT_v2.10 and later.

Input files
-----------
  clump_tau3_fcov5.in         tau0=1e3,        f_cov=5,  static (reference run)
  clump_tau4_fcov5.in         tau0=1e4,        f_cov=5,  static (high optical depth)
  clump_tau3_fcov20.in        tau0=1e3,        f_cov=20, static (dense covering)
  clump_tau3_fcov5_hubble.in  tau0=1e3,        f_cov=5,  Hubble expansion Vexp=200 km/s
  clump_tau3_fcov5_sigv.in    tau0=1e3,        f_cov=5,  clump sigma_v=50 km/s
  clump_tau3_fcov5_peel.in    tau0=1e3,        f_cov=5,  peel-off observer (129x129 image)

  clump_NHI18_fcov1.in        NHI=7.5e17 cm-2, f_cov=1,  per-clump column density (tau0~4.4e4)
  clump_NHI18_fcov5.in        NHI=7.5e17 cm-2, f_cov=5,  per-clump column density (tau0~4.4e4)
  clump_NHI18_fcov20.in       NHI=7.5e17 cm-2, f_cov=20, per-clump column density (tau0~4.4e4)

  The NHI cases use clump_radius=0.001 (10x smaller than the tau0 cases) and
  spectral_type='monochromatic' (photons injected at line centre).

How to run
----------
  cd LaRT_v2.00/examples/clump_sphere
  bash run.sh                            # runs all cases with NP=4
  # or individually:
  mpirun -np 4 ../../LaRT.x clump_tau3_fcov5.in

Output files
------------
  <base>.fits.gz            FITS spectrum: extensions [1] velocity, Jout, Jin
  <base>_obs.fits.gz        peel-off image cube (if save_peeloff = .true.)
  <base>_clumps.fits.gz     clump positions/velocities (if save_clump_info = .true.)

  _clumps.fits.gz BinTable columns: X, Y, Z [code units], VX, VY, VZ [km/s]
  Header keywords: N_CLUMPS, SPHERE_R, CL_RAD, F_VOL, F_COV, TAU0,
                   SIGMA_V, TEMP_CL, RHOKAP, CL_DFREQ, VTHERM, VOIGT_A,
                   RMAX, IN_FCOV, IN_FVOL, IN_NCL, IN_NHI, IN_NH, IN_TEMP

Analysis
--------
  python plot_clump.py                   # all runs
  python plot_clump.py clump_tau3_fcov5  # single run

  Produces per-run PDF with spectrum, peel-off image, and clump position
  scatter plot (z-slice), plus a multi-run comparison spectrum PDF.

Key parameters (namelist)
--------------------------
  par%use_clump_medium = .true.   ! selects clump-medium mode (v2.00)
  par%rmax             = 1.0      ! outer sphere radius [code units]
  par%clump_radius     = 0.01     ! individual clump radius [code units]
  par%clump_f_cov      = 5.0      ! line-of-sight covering factor  \
  par%clump_f_vol      = ...      !  or volume filling factor        >  specify one
  par%clump_N_clumps   = ...      !  or number of clumps            /
  par%clump_tau0       = 1.0e3    ! per-clump line-centre tau (centre -> surface)  \
  par%clump_NHI        = ...      !  or per-clump HI column density [cm^-2]         >  specify one
  par%clump_nH         = ...      !  or HI number density [cm^-3] (needs distance_unit) /
  par%clump_temperature = -1.0    ! clump T [K]; -1 uses par%temperature
  par%clump_sigma_v    = 0.0      ! Gaussian sigma of clump bulk velocity [km/s]
  par%velocity_type    = ''       ! 'hubble', 'constant_radial', 'ssh', etc.
  par%save_clump_info  = .true.   ! write *_clumps.fits.gz

Notes
-----
* RSA placement may be slow for f_vol > ~30%.  Use clump_N_clumps instead of
  clump_f_vol in that regime.
* f_cov = (3/4) * N_clumps * (clump_radius/rmax)^2; the effective optical
  depth through the sphere is approximately f_cov * tau0.
* clump_NHI is the column density of ONE individual clump (centre to surface).
  It is NOT the same as N_HImax, which is the system-level average column
  density along a sightline through the entire sphere.
  The equivalent tau0 is: tau0 = clump_NHI * sigma0 * phi(0, a_V),
  where sigma0 = line%cross0 / Dfreq [cm^2] is the line-centre cross-section.
  For T=1e4 K and clump_NHI=7.5e17 cm^-2: tau0 ~ 4.4e4.
* Opacity priority (first positive value wins): clump_tau0 > clump_NHI > clump_nH.
  clump_NHI does not require distance_unit; clump_nH does.
* The sightline-tau feature (par%save_sightline_tau) is not supported in clump
  mode (gives tau=0 everywhere because the Cartesian grid has rhokap=0).
* Multi-node runs: clump positions are generated by global rank 0 and broadcast
  so every node uses an identical layout.
